<title type="html"><![CDATA[AbsoluteY() Question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=451&amp;p=3254#p3254"><![CDATA[
Perhaps you have addressing modes mixed up in one or more opcodes.<br /><br />Not counting illegal opcodes, 0x19, 0x39, 0x59, 0x79, 0x99, 0xb9, 0xbe, 0xd9, 0xf9 use the absY addressing mode.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=115">hap</a> — Fri Jul 29, 2005 9:39 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
